text: find that I tend actually not to teach probably as well or as in-depth as I could because I don't want to be perceived as laying a wrap on someone. I don't want to be perceived as being some woo-woo Tibetan Buddhist who's doing all the chanting and the bells and all that, because I really don't identify with that, even though it has a place for some people. So I do talk about you a lot. I say, well, my teacher's really a very extraordinary person. See, that has its dangers, too. All of your points, I think, are totally appropriate.
